                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                One-to-one meetings with Bree during designated office hours or by appointment only. Reservation required.
                            %li
                                Meetings are booked in 30-minute increments (ranging from 30 minutes to 2 hours, on average). Parent(s) are invited to attend.
                            %li
                                Important: Counseling, research, and correspondence are limited to your office hours appointment. 
                            %li
                                $100/hour. Check made payable to academic stratEDGEy.
                            %li
                                Cancellation policy: Half-charge 
                            %li
                                During the school year, weekly office hours take place on Thursdays between 12:00-5:00 PM. 
                            %li
                                Office hours fill up on a first-come, first serve basis. For reservations, email stratedgey@gmail.com 

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                Focus and parameters of office hours
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                During office hours, Bree provides students with important information and personalized advice regarding a specific aspect of the college planning process. 
                            %li
                                Ideal for making decisions related to course planning, activity selection, standardized testing, school selection, etc. or creating a resume, essay brainstorm, brag sheet, etc.

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                How to maximize office hours
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Counseling, research, and correspondence are limited to your Office hours appointment. As with a follow up doctor’s visit, students may schedule an additional appointment(s) to receive further guidance and support. 
                            %li
                                In order to maximize your time, narrow your focus and come prepared by bringing a list of questions and any relevant paperwork (like a copy of your high school transcript).
